    "body": "Hi Matthias , \nThanks for your help in advance ! \nI was able to get a couple of things going1. I created a magic functionality as a Class as specified in  custommagics documentation  and using your repository as reference. Here is the link to my Git repo: https://github.com/vegabondx/savef. I have verified that if i run the file as %run savef.py it loads the magic function correctly. \n2. I was also able to make a PyPi package using flit command , again utilizing your repo as reference. I was able to create a package. \nHowever when I install the package , it does not \"install\" savef functionality in ipython by default. However when i do the following it works\n\n```\nIn [2]: %savef\nERROR:root:Line magic function `%savef` not found.\nIn [3]: %load_ext savef\nThe savef module is not an IPython extension.\nIn [4]: %savef -f\nStarting python file: `temp.py`\n```\n\n( i.e. working properly ) \n\nCould you let me know what I may be missing here ? Also is there any stylistic improvements I should make ? \n"
